<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
  <head>
    <title>Background Color Example</title>
    <style>
      body {
        background-color: #f2f2f2;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Hello, World!</h1>
    <p>This is an example of changing the background color using CSS.</p>
  </body>
</html>


This code sets the background color of the body element to a light gray color (#f2f2f2). You can change the color to any other valid CSS color value to customize the background color of your webpage.
